<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Razor">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>

    <!-- dotnet tool settings -->
    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>
    <ToolCommandName>mandocode</ToolCommandName>
    <PackageId>MandoCode</PackageId>

    <!-- NuGet metadata -->
    <Version>0.11.0</Version>
    <Authors>Armando Fernandez (DevMando)</Authors>
    <Description>Your AI coding assistant — run locally or in the cloud with Ollama. No API keys required. Just you and your code.</Description>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</RepositoryUrl>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageTags>ai;cli;coding-assistant;ollama;semantic-kernel;local-llm</PackageTags>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <PackageIcon>MC.png</PackageIcon>
    <ApplicationIcon>MC.ico</ApplicationIcon>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
v0.11.0 — A release about trust

When you tell MandoCode to stop, it should stop. When it's working, it shouldn't silently freeze. And when it searches the web, the search should actually work. This release fixes every way we found those promises could break — each one discovered by building real projects with MandoCode itself.

New:
- Web search that doesn't randomly fail. Search works out of the box with no key, but the free DuckDuckGo service sometimes blocks busy users mid-session. You can now add a free Tavily key (about 1,000 searches a month) with: /config set tavilyKey YOUR-KEY — searches become faster and more reliable, and DuckDuckGo stays as the backup. Skip it and nothing changes; if a search ever does get blocked, the assistant explains the option right in the chat. The assistant also now treats live questions — weather, news, scores, latest versions — as search-first, instead of telling you about its training cutoff and suggesting you Google it yourself.
- Change settings without losing your session. /config set lets you adjust the model, temperature, timeouts, and more mid-conversation — no restart, history kept.

Fixed:
- "Stop" now means stop. Cancelling a plan or request used to politely ask the AI to stop — and sometimes it just kept going, writing files you'd already said no to. Now the app itself refuses to run anything further the moment you cancel.
- No more silent freezes. We closed every way we found a session could hang forever: prompts that fought over your keyboard, a watchdog that fell asleep after a settings change, and approvals that couldn't be escaped. Esc always works now.
- The AI can finally see large files. It used to read only the top of long files and guess at the rest, then loop on failed edits. It now reads exactly the section it's working on and knows where to continue.
- Local models stopped "forgetting" your instructions. Ollama's small default memory window was silently dropping older context as conversations grew; MandoCode now sizes it to your hardware automatically.
- Finished work stays finished. After a plan completes, the AI can no longer bulldoze the result with "improvements" you didn't ask for, or propose endless follow-up plans.
- Clearer guidance when a reply gets cut off: the warning now tells you which limit you actually hit and the one setting that fixes it.

Polish:
- Every menu speaks the same color language — green means go, gold means redirect, red means destructive — so you can tell how consequential a choice is at a glance. Arrow keys never drop a press.
- /model is now a true quick switch: pick a model, done.
- Under the hood: 393 automated tests now guard all of the above.
    </PackageReleaseNotes>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="HtmlAgilityPack" Version="1.11.72" />
    <PackageReference Include="Markdig" Version="1.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.FileSystemGlobbing" Version="10.0.3" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel" Version="1.72.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.Ollama" Version="1.72.0-alpha" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions" Version="10.5.2" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI" Version="10.5.2" />
    <PackageReference Include="ModelContextProtocol" Version="1.3.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="NAudio" Version="2.2.1" />
    <PackageReference Include="RazorConsole.Core" Version="0.5.0-alpha.20260225-7c02f3c" />
    <PackageReference Include="YamlDotNet" Version="16.2.1" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <EmbeddedResource Include="Audio\**\*.mp3" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\..\README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
    <None Include="MC.png" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
